result.execSummary:
The defendant Jaylen S Washington was found guilty of the following charge(s) in this case.

  • Carrying Concealed Weapon. This is not a criminal offense and results only in a money penalty for this offense.

Notice to employers: It may be a violation of state law to discriminate against a job applicant because of an arrest or conviction record. Generally speaking, an employer may refuse to hire an applicant on the basis of a conviction only if the circumstances of the conviction substantially relate to the particular job. For more information, see Wisconsin Statute 111.335 and the Department of Workforce Development's publication, Arrest and Conviction Records under the Law.

records.addlTxt: CORRECTION: Judge Konkol presided over Branch 13 on September 1st, 2022

Defendant Jaylen S Washington in court.  Attorney Corey R. Flynn in court for Jaylen S Washington.  Prosecuting attorney Thomas Hasle in court for the State of Wisconsin. 
Case in court for a pre-trial conference. Pursuant to negotiations, and on motion of the County, Court amends charge to Carry Concealed Weapon pursuant to County Ordinance 63.015.  
Defendant enters a no contest plea  to the amended charge.  Court finds defendant guilty.
Court ordered defendant pay a forfeiture of $100.00 inclusive of costs.  Payable in 60 DAYS or civil judgment.
No possession of dangerous weapons or firearms.

Defendant Jaylen S Washington in court.    Madeline Witte, under the student practice rule, appeared with A.D.A. Jon R Josephsen appeared for the State of Wisconsin.
Defendant advised that this case is assigned to Reserve Judge, Branch 13.
Court reviewed the complaint and found probable cause. Defendant received a copy of the complaint and was advised of right to counsel and maximum penalties.  Court entered a plea of not guilty on behalf of the Defendant. Court reserves Defendant's right to file a substitution of judge pursuant to Sec. 971.20 right to challenge probable cause and to have complaint read until Defendant's next scheduled court appearance. Defendant IS Public Defender eligible. Defendant is ordered to provide the public defender's office with the next court date.  
The case is adjourned to Br. 13 for a Pretrial Conference.  Pre-trial conference scheduled for September 1, 2022 at 08:30 am.
Summons mailed.  Defendant ordered into room 221 Safety Building on 08/12/2022@1pm
